Introduction¶

The TMDb movie data set contains information related to over 10000 movies. The data includes details of movies like genre to which a particular movie belongs, budget put in, revenue generated etc. These particulars have been noted for over a span of 52 years.

Based on the given dataset the following investigation can be done:

  1. Genre trends over the years in relation to budget, revenue and profit percent.
  2. Overall budget, revenue and profit percent trends over the years for movie industry.
  3. Leading Production Companies in the movie business and their budget, revenue and profit trends

Data Cleaning¶

Performing the above operations has shown that there is one duplicate value and too many null values in the given dataset. To carry out further investigation we need to clean this to obtain reliable results.

Dropping out null values as it is, is first approach. But here we can see that columns namely homepage, tagline and keywords have very high number of null values. Deleting these null values will make us lose major chunk of data and since they are not involved in any of our investigation dropping these columns will be an ideal approach.

After deletion of the said columns we can drop the null values.

There is also an issue with the budget column. ".describe()" operation shows that 50% of the values lies within the zero budget which seems incorrect not at all reliable hence we will only include data with budget of more than 1000

The analysis also includes showing profit percent and profit so we will make new columns and add to the data set.

Also few columns have multiple strings like genres and production companies. It will be split and the first word will be used for analysis

Clearing Duplicates and undesired columns

In [7]:
df.drop_duplicates(inplace=True)
In [8]:
df.duplicated().sum()
Out[8]:
0
In [9]:
df_cleaned = df.drop(columns=['homepage', 'tagline', 'keywords','overview'])

Getting the first keyword for genres and production companies by splitting strings.

In [12]:
df_cleaned['genres'] = df['genres'].str.split('|').str[0]
In [13]:
df_cleaned['production_companies'] = df['production_companies'].str.split('|').str[0]

Calculating profit and profit percent and adding them as new columns in our dataset

In [14]:
df_cleaned['profit'] = df_cleaned['revenue'] - df_cleaned['budget']
df_cleaned['profit_percent'] = ((df_cleaned['revenue'] - df_cleaned['budget']) * 100 )/df_cleaned['budget']

Final step here will be considering budget above 1000 which is more realistic data

In [15]:
df_clean= df_cleaned[df_cleaned['budget'] > 1000]

Exploring genre trends over the years in relation to budget, revenue and profit percent.¶

  • Budget put in for a genre on an average.

  • Genres that gave huge profits in terms of profit percent

The above graph shows 'Popular Genres' in terms of number of movies made in a particular genre.

The graph above shows 'Yearwise Popular Genres' i.e. which genre ruled in a particular year.

Conclusions¶

Exploring genre trends over the years in relation to budget, revenue and profit percent.

  • In these graphs we could visualize the genre trends in relation to budget revenue and profit percent.
  • We could also see genres that were favoured in each year.
  • Data showed that the most number of movies were made in drama genre, average budget required in adventure was highest while animation made most revenue on an average
  • It could also be concluded that horror made the most profitable genre.

Exploring overall budget, revenue and profit percent trends over the years for movie industry.

  • The graphs here showed that profits were increasing year by year though it was not always a smooth upwards ride.
  • The top box office hit was made in 2009, average budget of total movies by release year was highest in 2004, while revenue earned by movies on an average by release year was highest in 2015.
  • The year 1999 was the most profitable year for the movie industry.

Exploring Leading Production Companies in the business and their profit trends.

  • We found that the leading production company was Universal Pictures, highest average budget was put in the year 2012 nd most profitable year was 1975.
  • The revenue earned on an average seems to have an increasing trend.

Limitations¶

  • Almost 50% of the values in budget column were 0 and a few values were below 200 which is not reliable.
  • Deleting these records might deviate from the accurate results which could have been achieved by correct data collection.
